 and to issue a challenge to all Canadians to become fully alive as individuals and as citizens to both the dangers and the potentialities of the post-Hiroshima world. This book is social criticism at its best—alert, authoritative, urgent.This common concern brought the authors together in the planning of an unusual book. The finished work shows that they share a left-of-centre viewpoint; it also shows that they write as individuals. The essays, it is confidently predicted, will be found greatly stimulating for the high quality of their analysis by serious readers of all persuasions who are concerned about the Canadian society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / World / Canadian.2bisacsh1 aBreton, Albert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrownstone, Meyer, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCallard, Keith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCompton, Neil, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGordon, H. Scott, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrant, George, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGreene, Adam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJamieson, Stuart, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcnaught, Kenneth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMorgan, John S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOliver, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOliver, Michael, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPorter, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRosenbluth, G., econtributor.4ctb4ht